menu "QR decoder spike"

    config QR_DECODE_SQUARE
        int "PPA output / QR decode square size (px, 0 = auto)"
        default 0
        range 0 800
        help
            Side length of the square frame the camera PPA produces and that
            the QR consumer (quirc) runs on. This is the Phase-1 spike's master
            knob: smaller = faster quirc + less PSRAM traffic, bounded below by
            >=3 px/module for the worst-case QR.

            0 means "auto": use the shorter logical display dimension (the
            previous hardcoded behavior). Any non-zero value overrides it, so
            the sweep can be driven per-build from sdkconfig with no source
            edits. Typical sweep points: 480, 320, 240.

endmenu
